1
00:00:00,835 --> 00:00:05,130
[ MUSIC ]

2
00:00:05,130 --> 00:00:06,674
CAPTAIN'S LOG.

3
00:00:06,674 --> 00:00:10,594
OUR POSITION, ORBITING PSI 2000,
AN ANCIENT WORLD,

4
00:00:10,594 --> 00:00:13,263
NOW A FROZEN WASTELAND,
ABOUT TO RIP APART

5
00:00:13,263 --> 00:00:15,140
IN ITS DEATH THROES.

6
00:00:15,140 --> 00:00:18,226
OUR MISSION, PICK UP
A SCIENTIFIC PARTY BELOW,

7
00:00:18,226 --> 00:00:23,315
OBSERVE THE DISINTEGRATION
OF THE PLANET.

8
00:00:50,009 --> 00:00:51,969
CHECK OUT
THE LIFE-SUPPORT SYSTEMS.

9
00:00:51,969 --> 00:00:55,138
RIGHT, SIR.

10
00:01:01,186 --> 00:01:04,398
[ MUSIC ]

11
00:01:10,487 --> 00:01:14,491
[ BEEPING ]

12
00:01:16,702 --> 00:01:20,288
ALL LIFE SYSTEMS WERE OFF, SIR.

13
00:01:20,288 --> 00:01:23,000
SOMEONE STRANGLED THIS WOMAN.

14
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:24,334
THE OTHER FOUR ARE BACK THERE.

15
00:01:24,334 --> 00:01:25,252
DEAD?

16
00:01:25,252 --> 00:01:26,211
RIGHT, SIR.

17
00:01:26,211 --> 00:01:27,504
ENGINEER AT HIS POST?

18
00:01:27,504 --> 00:01:30,382
HE'S FROZEN THERE
LIKE HE DIDN'T CARE.

19
00:01:30,382 --> 00:01:32,133
THE REST?

20
00:01:32,133 --> 00:01:35,637
WELL, BETTER LOOK FOR YOURSELF,
MR. SPOCK.

21
00:01:35,637 --> 00:01:38,766
ONE MAN WAS TAKING A SHOWER
FULLY CLOTHED.

22
00:01:38,766 --> 00:01:42,310
[ MUSIC ]

23
00:01:56,075 --> 00:01:59,327
[ BUZZING ]

24
00:02:52,131 --> 00:02:54,508
BE CERTAIN WE EXPOSE OURSELVES
TO NOTHING.

25
00:02:54,508 --> 00:02:54,842
[ BEEPING ]

26
00:02:54,842 --> 00:02:56,802
SPOCK HERE.
DO YOU READ, ENTERPRISE?

27
00:02:56,802 --> 00:02:58,053
Kirk, affirmative.

28
00:02:58,053 --> 00:02:59,888
ALL STATION PERSONNEL ARE DEAD.

29
00:02:59,888 --> 00:03:01,015
What caused it?

30
00:03:01,015 --> 00:03:02,724
UNKNOWN, CAPTAIN.

31
00:03:02,724 --> 00:03:06,728
IT'S LIKE NOTHING
WE'VE DEALT WITH BEFORE.

32
00:03:08,939 --> 00:03:12,693
[ MUSIC ]

33
00:03:13,819 --> 00:03:17,823
SPACE, THE FINAL FRONTIER.

34
00:03:17,823 --> 00:03:21,535
THESE ARE THE VOYAGES
OF THE STARSHIP<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

35
00:03:21,535 --> 00:03:26,623
IT'S FIVE-YEAR MISSION:
TO EXPLORE STRANGE NEW WORLDS,

36
00:03:26,623 --> 00:03:30,502
TO SEEK OUT NEW LIFE
AND NEW CIVILIZATIONS,

37
00:03:30,502 --> 00:03:34,798
TO BOLDLY GO
WHERE NO MAN HAS GONE BEFORE.

38
00:03:59,406 --> 00:04:02,659
[ MUSIC ]

39
00:04:06,580 --> 00:04:10,375
CAPTAIN'S LOG: STARDATE 1704.2.

40
00:04:10,375 --> 00:04:12,293
THE SCIENCE PARTY
WE WERE TO HAVE PICKED UP

41
00:04:12,293 --> 00:04:13,712
HAS BEEN FOUND DEAD.

42
00:04:13,712 --> 00:04:16,048
LIFE SUPPORT SYSTEMS
HAD BEEN TURNED OFF.

43
00:04:16,048 --> 00:04:18,258
STATION PERSONNEL,
FROZEN TO DEATH.

44
00:04:18,258 --> 00:04:20,260
CONDITIONS HIGHLY UNUSUAL.

45
00:04:20,260 --> 00:04:23,180
MEANWHILE, WE REMAIN IN ORBIT
TO COMPLETE OUR MISSION,

46
00:04:23,180 --> 00:04:29,019
CLOSE SCIENTIFIC MEASUREMENT
OF THE BREAKUP OF THIS PLANET.

47
00:04:36,317 --> 00:04:37,986
YOU RECEIVED MY SIGNAL,
MR. SCOTT?

48
00:04:37,986 --> 00:04:38,904
YES, SIR.

49
00:04:38,904 --> 00:04:40,280
DECONTAMINATE.

50
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:43,117
[ BUZZING ]

51
00:04:46,536 --> 00:04:49,706
[ WHISTLE ]

52
00:04:49,706 --> 00:04:50,832
CAPTAIN HERE.

53
00:04:50,832 --> 00:04:52,251
SPOCK AND TORMOLEN ABOARD, SIR.

54
00:04:52,251 --> 00:04:53,460
WE'RE HOLDING THEM
IN THE CHAMBER

55
00:04:53,460 --> 00:04:54,962
FOR DECONTAMINATION.

56
00:04:54,962 --> 00:04:56,671
BETTER HAVE MEDICINE
LOOK THEM OVER, TOO.

57
00:04:56,671 --> 00:04:58,966
TELL MR. SPOCK I'LL MEET HIM
THERE IN 10 MINUTES.

58
00:04:58,966 --> 00:05:01,760
KIRK OUT.

59
00:05:06,306 --> 00:05:07,057
YOU'RE FINE, JOE.

60
00:05:07,057 --> 00:05:11,603
UP AND OUT OF THERE.

61
00:05:11,603 --> 00:05:13,188
MR. SPOCK?

62
00:05:13,188 --> 00:05:16,858
[ FAINT SIREN SOUND ]

63
00:05:16,858 --> 00:05:20,821
[ BEEPING ]

64
00:05:20,821 --> 00:05:24,241
YOUR PULSE IS 242.

65
00:05:24,241 --> 00:05:27,786
YOUR BLOOD PRESSURE
IS PRACTICALLY NONEXISTENT,

66
00:05:27,786 --> 00:05:32,624
ASSUMING YOU CALL THAT GREEN
STUFF IN YOUR VEINS BLOOD.

67
00:05:32,624 --> 00:05:34,626
THE READINGS ARE PERFECTLY
NORMAL FOR ME, DOCTOR,

68
00:05:34,626 --> 00:05:35,294
THANK YOU.

69
00:05:35,294 --> 00:05:38,005
AND AS FOR MY ANATOMY
BEING DIFFERENT FROM YOURS,

70
00:05:38,005 --> 00:05:39,881
I AM DELIGHTED.

71
00:05:39,881 --> 00:05:43,677
[ MUSIC ]

72
00:05:44,552 --> 00:05:45,220
CAPTAIN.

73
00:05:45,220 --> 00:05:45,929
HOW ARE THEY?

74
00:05:45,929 --> 00:05:47,097
THEY'RE FINE, JIM.

75
00:05:47,097 --> 00:05:48,932
TERRIBLE, CAPTAIN.

76
00:05:48,932 --> 00:05:49,975
IT WAS TERRIBLE.

77
00:05:49,975 --> 00:05:53,603
THEY WERE JUST SITTING
LIKE THEY DIDN'T CARE.

78
00:05:53,603 --> 00:05:55,939
WHATEVER WAS HAPPENING,
THEY DIDN'T CARE.

79
00:05:55,939 --> 00:05:57,149
I KEEP WONDERING--

80
00:05:57,149 --> 00:06:00,694
YOU KEEP WONDERING
IF MAN WAS MEANT TO BE OUT HERE.

81
00:06:00,694 --> 00:06:04,614
YOU KEEP WONDERING,
YOU KEEP SIGNING ON.

82
00:06:04,614 --> 00:06:06,867
ANY GUESSES, MR. SPOCK?

83
00:06:06,867 --> 00:06:08,327
ANY IDEA OF WHAT HAPPENED
DOWN THERE?

84
00:06:08,327 --> 00:06:09,744
I WISH I COULD SAY, CAPTAIN.

85
00:06:09,744 --> 00:06:11,997
THE CIRCUMSTANCES
WERE QUITE BIZARRE,

86
00:06:11,997 --> 00:06:14,499
HOWEVER OUR RECORD TAPES
MAY SHOW US SOMETHING.

87
00:06:14,499 --> 00:06:16,043
SIX DEAD.

88
00:06:16,043 --> 00:06:18,128
SIX PEOPLE DEAD.

89
00:06:18,128 --> 00:06:20,005
YOU BETTER GET SOME REST.

90
00:06:20,005 --> 00:06:20,839
YES, SIR.

91
00:06:20,839 --> 00:06:22,174
SET UP THOSE TAPES, MR. SPOCK.

92
00:06:22,174 --> 00:06:26,385
WE'LL SEE
IF THE ANSWERS ARE ON THERE.

93
00:06:28,555 --> 00:06:29,931
THE LAB STATUS REPORT, DOCTOR.

94
00:06:29,931 --> 00:06:31,141
OH, THANK YOU, CHRISTINE.

95
00:06:31,141 --> 00:06:34,561
[ MUSIC ]

96
00:06:36,021 --> 00:06:40,150
[ RATTLING SOUND ]

97
00:06:40,150 --> 00:06:41,609
NEXT TAPE, PLEASE.

98
00:06:41,609 --> 00:06:43,111
SPECTRO-ANALYSIS TAPE, SIR.

99
00:06:43,111 --> 00:06:45,446
THANK YOU.

100
00:06:45,446 --> 00:06:48,158
[ FAINT SIREN SOUND ]

101
00:06:54,915 --> 00:06:57,251
ALMOST AS THOUGH
THEY WERE IRRATIONAL, DRUGGED.

102
00:06:57,251 --> 00:06:59,002
AN ENGINEER SITTING THERE
APPARENTLY OBLIVIOUS

103
00:06:59,002 --> 00:06:59,669
TO EVERYTHING.

104
00:06:59,669 --> 00:07:00,587
A WOMAN STRANGLED,

105
00:07:00,587 --> 00:07:02,672
A CREWMAN WITH A PHASER PISTOL
IN HIS HAND.

106
00:07:02,672 --> 00:07:04,216
HE'D USED THE COMPUTER ROOM

107
00:07:04,216 --> 00:07:05,675
AS IF IT WERE AN AMUSEMENT
GALLERY.

108
00:07:05,675 --> 00:07:08,762
AND A FULLY CLOTHED MAN
FROZEN TO DEATH IN A SHOWER.

109
00:07:08,762 --> 00:07:13,183
IF THE IMAGE WASN'T SO UGLY,
IT'D BE LAUGHABLE.

110
00:07:13,183 --> 00:07:14,976
NOT EVEN A THEORY, GENTLEMEN?

111
00:07:14,976 --> 00:07:17,437
DEFINITELY NOT DRUGS
OR INTOXICATION.

112
00:07:17,437 --> 00:07:20,274
THE BIOANALYSIS ON THE TAPES
PROVE THAT CONCLUSIVELY.

113
00:07:20,274 --> 00:07:23,193
IT COULD BE SOME FORM OF SPACE
MADNESS WE'VE NEVER HEARD OF,

114
00:07:23,193 --> 00:07:25,195
BUT IT WOULD HAVE TO
BE CAUSED BY SOMETHING.

115
00:07:25,195 --> 00:07:27,739
OUR SPECTRO-READINGS
SHOWED NO CONTAMINATION,

116
00:07:27,739 --> 00:07:29,574
NO UNUSUAL ELEMENTS PRESENT.

117
00:07:29,574 --> 00:07:31,993
OR AT LEAST NONE
YOUR TRICORDERS COULD REGISTER.

118
00:07:31,993 --> 00:07:33,453
INSTRUMENTS REGISTER
ONLY THOSE THINGS

119
00:07:33,453 --> 00:07:35,289
THEY'RE DESIGNED TO REGISTER.

120
00:07:35,289 --> 00:07:38,208
SPACE STILL CONTAINS
INFINITE UNKNOWNS.

121
00:07:38,208 --> 00:07:40,627
EARTH SCIENCE NEEDS
THE CLOSEST POSSIBLE MEASUREMENT

122
00:07:40,627 --> 00:07:42,087
OF THE BREAKUP OF THIS PLANET.

123
00:07:42,087 --> 00:07:43,880
TO DO THIS,
WE NEED THE<i> ENTERPRISE</i>

124
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:45,548
IN A CRITICALLY TIGHT ORBIT.

125
00:07:45,548 --> 00:07:46,883
QUESTION:

126
00:07:46,883 --> 00:07:48,802
COULD WHAT HAPPENED DOWN THERE
TO THOSE PEOPLE

127
00:07:48,802 --> 00:07:54,682
CREATE ANY UNUSUAL DANGER
TO THIS VESSEL AND CREW?

128
00:07:54,682 --> 00:07:56,435
WE WILL NEED TOP EFFICIENCY,
CAPTAIN.

129
00:07:56,435 --> 00:07:58,019
IT'LL BE A TRICKY ORBIT.

130
00:07:58,019 --> 00:08:01,356
WHEN THE PLANET BEGINS TO GO,
THERE MAY BE DRASTIC CHANGES

131
00:08:01,356 --> 00:08:05,152
IN GRAVITY, MASS,
MAGNETIC FIELD.

132
00:08:05,152 --> 00:08:07,654
THE PURPOSE OF A BRIEFING,
GENTLEMEN, IS TO GET THE ANSWERS

133
00:08:07,654 --> 00:08:10,407
BASED ON YOUR ABILITIES
AND EXPERIENCE.

134
00:08:10,407 --> 00:08:13,327
IN A CRITICAL ORBIT,
THERE'S NO TIME FOR SURPRISE.

135
00:08:13,327 --> 00:08:14,535
UNLESS YOU PEOPLE ON THE BRIDGE

136
00:08:14,535 --> 00:08:16,579
START TAKING SHOWERS
WITH YOUR CLOTHES ON,

137
00:08:16,579 --> 00:08:19,291
MY ENGINES CAN PULL US
OUT OF ANYTHING.

138
00:08:19,291 --> 00:08:21,501
WE'LL BE WARPING OUT OF ORBIT
WITHIN A HALF SECOND

139
00:08:21,501 --> 00:08:22,794
OF GETTING YOUR COMMAND.

140
00:08:22,794 --> 00:08:24,796
Bridge to Captain.

141
00:08:24,796 --> 00:08:25,797
KIRK HERE.

142
00:08:25,797 --> 00:08:28,091
Scanners report
sudden four-degree shift

143
00:08:28,091 --> 00:08:30,344
in planet magnetic field.

144
00:08:30,344 --> 00:08:33,013
A change in mass also, sir.

145
00:08:33,013 --> 00:08:34,348
IT'S BEGINNING.

146
00:08:34,348 --> 00:08:36,933
UNUSUALLY RAPID SHIFTS.

147
00:08:36,933 --> 00:08:38,310
ON OUR WAY, LIEUTENANT.

148
00:08:38,310 --> 00:08:41,813
I'LL HOLD YOU
TO THAT HALF SECOND, SCOTTY.

149
00:08:45,775 --> 00:08:50,071
[ FAINT SIREN SOUND ]

150
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:07,881
[ MUSIC ]

151
00:09:12,677 --> 00:09:13,470
FOIL.

152
00:09:13,470 --> 00:09:14,804
IT'S A RAPIER.

153
00:09:14,804 --> 00:09:15,930
A THIN SWORD.

154
00:09:15,930 --> 00:09:17,015
ALL RIGHT.

155
00:09:17,015 --> 00:09:18,725
SO WHAT DO YOU DO WITH IT?

156
00:09:18,725 --> 00:09:20,643
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
WHAT DO YOU DO WITH IT?

157
00:09:20,643 --> 00:09:22,020
SELF-DEFENSE?

158
00:09:22,020 --> 00:09:23,397
MAYHEM?

159
00:09:23,397 --> 00:09:24,898
SHISH KEBAB?

160
00:09:24,898 --> 00:09:26,358
YOU PRACTICE.

161
00:09:26,358 --> 00:09:27,775
FOR WHAT?

162
00:09:27,775 --> 00:09:30,611
HI, JOEY.

163
00:09:30,611 --> 00:09:32,030
LAST WEEK, IT WAS BOTANY

164
00:09:32,030 --> 00:09:33,948
HE WAS TRYING TO GET ME
INTERESTED IN.

165
00:09:33,948 --> 00:09:35,616
I WAS SUPPOSED
TO BE COLLECTING LEAVES,

166
00:09:35,616 --> 00:09:36,910
PLANT SPECIMENS.

167
00:09:36,910 --> 00:09:38,495
YOUR ATTITUDE IS ALL WRONG.

168
00:09:38,495 --> 00:09:41,248
FENCING TONES THE MUSCLE,
SHARPENS THE EYE,

169
00:09:41,248 --> 00:09:43,083
IMPROVES THE POSTURE.

170
00:09:43,083 --> 00:09:45,919
YOU TELL HIM, JOEY.
EXPLAIN TO HIM.

171
00:09:47,670 --> 00:09:51,341
HEY, JOEY.
YOU FEELING ALL RIGHT?

172
00:09:51,341 --> 00:09:52,509
GET OFF ME.

173
00:09:52,509 --> 00:09:54,594
YOU DON'T RANK ME,
AND YOU DON'T HAVE POINTED EARS.

174
00:09:54,594 --> 00:09:57,264
SO JUST GET OFF MY NECK!

175
00:09:57,264 --> 00:09:58,598
WHAT'S WITH HIM?

176
00:09:58,598 --> 00:10:00,517
NOTHING.

177
00:10:00,517 --> 00:10:03,103
[ MUSIC ]

178
00:10:03,103 --> 00:10:04,354
[ WHISTLE ]

179
00:10:04,354 --> 00:10:05,439
Attention.

180
00:10:05,439 --> 00:10:07,399
Engine room on standby alert.

181
00:10:07,399 --> 00:10:09,276
All duty personnel
to the bridge.

182
00:10:09,276 --> 00:10:12,028
Acknowledge.

183
00:10:12,028 --> 00:10:14,406
YOU SURE
YOU'RE ALL RIGHT NOW, JOE?

184
00:10:14,406 --> 00:10:15,532
WE'VE GOT TO LEAVE.

185
00:10:15,532 --> 00:10:18,159
WE'RE ALL A BUNCH OF HYPOCRITES,
STICKING OUR NOSES

186
00:10:18,159 --> 00:10:21,371
INTO SOMETHING
THAT WE'VE GOT NO BUSINESS.

187
00:10:21,371 --> 00:10:22,956
WHAT ARE WE DOING OUT HERE,
ANYWAY?

188
00:10:22,956 --> 00:10:26,960
TAKE IT EASY, JOE.

189
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:29,379
WE BRING PAIN
AND TROUBLE WITH US,

190
00:10:29,379 --> 00:10:31,839
LEAVE MEN AND WOMEN
STUCK OUT IN FREEZING PLANETS

191
00:10:31,839 --> 00:10:33,467
UNTIL THEY DIE.

192
00:10:33,467 --> 00:10:35,552
WHAT ARE WE DOING
OUT HERE IN SPACE?

193
00:10:35,552 --> 00:10:37,011
GOOD?

194
00:10:37,011 --> 00:10:38,763
WHAT GOOD?

195
00:10:38,763 --> 00:10:41,641
WE'RE POLLUTING IT,
DESTROYING IT.

196
00:10:41,641 --> 00:10:44,227
WE'VE GOT NO BUSINESS
BEING OUT HERE, NO BUSINESS.

197
00:10:44,227 --> 00:10:46,813
-TAKE IT EASY, JOE.
-NOW, CALM DOWN.

198
00:10:46,813 --> 00:10:49,357
IF A MAN WAS SUPPOSED TO FLY,
HE'D HAVE WINGS.

199
00:10:49,357 --> 00:10:50,942
IF HE WAS SUPPOSED
TO BE OUT IN SPACE,

200
00:10:50,942 --> 00:10:52,693
HE WOULDN'T NEED AIR TO BREATHE,

201
00:10:52,693 --> 00:10:53,945
WOULDN'T NEED LIFE
SUPPORT SYSTEMS

202
00:10:53,945 --> 00:10:55,322
TO KEEP HIM
FROM FREEZING TO DEATH.

203
00:10:55,322 --> 00:10:57,240
HEY, JOEY,
PUT THE KNIFE DOWN, HUH?

204
00:10:57,240 --> 00:10:58,908
YOU'RE ALL STEAMED UP, JOE.

205
00:10:58,908 --> 00:11:01,620
WE DON'T BELONG HERE.

206
00:11:01,620 --> 00:11:05,415
IT'S NOT OURS. NOT OURS.

207
00:11:05,415 --> 00:11:09,961
DESTROYING AND WATCHING.

208
00:11:09,961 --> 00:11:12,339
WE DON'T BELONG.

209
00:11:12,339 --> 00:11:14,549
I DON'T BELONG.

210
00:11:14,549 --> 00:11:18,052
SIX PEOPLE DIED DOWN THERE.

211
00:11:18,052 --> 00:11:21,348
WHY DO I DESERVE TO LIVE?

212
00:11:21,348 --> 00:11:22,390
WHAT ARE YOU DOING, JOE?

213
00:11:22,390 --> 00:11:23,724
HEY, JOEY, PUT THE KNIFE DOWN.

214
00:11:23,724 --> 00:11:24,892
-DON'T BE A FOOL, JOEY.
-LET GO OF ME.

215
00:11:24,892 --> 00:11:25,768
YOU'RE JUST GETTING IN A SWEAT
ABOUT--

216
00:11:25,768 --> 00:11:26,894
LET GO. LET GO.

217
00:11:26,894 --> 00:11:28,021
LET ME HAVE THE KNIFE.

218
00:11:28,021 --> 00:11:29,439
LET ME GO.

219
00:11:29,439 --> 00:11:33,943
JOEY, DON'T BE A FOOL.

220
00:11:33,943 --> 00:11:36,988
JOEY.

221
00:11:36,988 --> 00:11:39,907
JOEY, GIVE ME THE KNIFE.

222
00:11:39,907 --> 00:11:42,743
[ MUSIC ]

223
00:11:49,917 --> 00:11:50,751
EMERGENCY.

224
00:11:50,751 --> 00:11:52,128
REC ROOM AREA THREE NINE.

225
00:11:52,128 --> 00:11:54,339
WE NEED MEDICS.

226
00:11:54,339 --> 00:11:57,551
[ RATTLING SOUND ]

227
00:11:57,551 --> 00:12:01,221
[ MUSIC ]

228
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:07,310
CAPTAIN'S LOG, SUPPLEMENTAL.

229
00:12:07,310 --> 00:12:08,853
OUR ORBIT, TIGHTENING.

230
00:12:08,853 --> 00:12:11,147
OUR NEED FOR EFFICIENCY,
CRITICAL.

231
00:12:11,147 --> 00:12:14,526
BUT UNKNOWN TO US, A TOTALLY NEW
AND UNUSUAL DISEASE

232
00:12:14,526 --> 00:12:16,236
HAS BEEN BROUGHT ABOARD.

233
00:12:16,236 --> 00:12:17,736
RELATIVE GRAVITY INCREASING,
SIR.

234
00:12:17,736 --> 00:12:19,030
COMPENSATE, MR. RILEY.

235
00:12:19,030 --> 00:12:19,738
YES, SIR.

236
00:12:19,738 --> 00:12:21,616
MAGNETIC FIELD
CONTINUING TO SHIFT, SIR.

237
00:12:21,616 --> 00:12:25,119
PLANET CONTINUING TO SHRINK
IN MASS.

238
00:12:27,955 --> 00:12:28,873
MR. SPOCK?

239
00:12:28,873 --> 00:12:29,916
ALL SCANNING STATIONS MANNED,

240
00:12:29,916 --> 00:12:31,876
ALL RECORDERS FUNCTIONING,
CAPTAIN.

241
00:12:31,876 --> 00:12:35,255
ORBIT STEADY NOW, SIR.

242
00:12:35,255 --> 00:12:37,090
OBVIOUSLY, THIS PLANET
IS CONDENSING

243
00:12:37,090 --> 00:12:40,093
MORE RAPIDLY THAN EXPECTED.

244
00:12:40,093 --> 00:12:41,595
A VALUABLE STUDY.

245
00:12:41,595 --> 00:12:45,181
WE MAY BE SEEING
EARTH'S DISTANT FUTURE.

246
00:12:45,181 --> 00:12:46,641
BEFORE ITS SUN WENT DARK,

247
00:12:46,641 --> 00:12:49,394
THIS PLANET
WAS REMARKABLY SIMILAR TO YOURS.

248
00:12:49,394 --> 00:12:51,563
HELM ANSWERING NICELY, CAPTAIN.

249
00:12:51,563 --> 00:12:55,316
GOOD.

250
00:12:59,696 --> 00:13:02,365
COMMUNICATION STATUS, CAPTAIN.

251
00:13:02,365 --> 00:13:03,782
[ MUSIC ]

252
00:13:03,782 --> 00:13:07,328
[ RATTLING SOUND ]

253
00:13:12,459 --> 00:13:13,543
TORMOLEN'S RECORD?

254
00:13:13,543 --> 00:13:15,712
PSYCHIATRIC FILE
AND PERSONALITY QUOTIENTS.

255
00:13:15,712 --> 00:13:17,589
WAS HE TRYING TO KILL HIMSELF?

256
00:13:17,589 --> 00:13:21,384
IT'S DOUBTFUL HE MEANT TO.
HE WAS CONFUSED, SELF-TORTURED.

257
00:13:21,384 --> 00:13:23,844
DOESN'T SOUND
LIKE THE MAN I KNOW.

258
00:13:23,844 --> 00:13:27,265
HIS CAPACITY FOR SELF-DOUBT
HAS ALWAYS BEEN RATHER HIGH.

259
00:13:27,265 --> 00:13:29,267
WHAT PUZZLES ME IS
WHAT BROUGHT IT TO THE SURFACE

260
00:13:29,267 --> 00:13:33,187
WITH SO MUCH FORCE.

261
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:42,280
[ BREATHING ]

262
00:14:02,759 --> 00:14:05,886
HIS BREATHING RATE IS DROPPING,
DOCTOR.

263
00:14:05,886 --> 00:14:09,432
COMPENSATE WITH THE RESPIRATOR.

264
00:14:11,685 --> 00:14:16,648
[ RESPIRATOR SOUND ]

265
00:14:18,232 --> 00:14:21,611
STAND BY TO CLOSE.

266
00:14:29,369 --> 00:14:33,122
CLOSING.

267
00:14:39,045 --> 00:14:42,590
[ ALARM ]

268
00:14:42,590 --> 00:14:43,257
WHAT IS IT?

269
00:14:43,257 --> 00:14:44,925
RELATIVE GRAVITY INCREASE,
SIR.

270
00:14:44,925 --> 00:14:47,094
LIKE THE PLANET REACHED OUT
AND YANKED AT US.

271
00:14:47,094 --> 00:14:50,557
COMPENSATE.

272
00:14:54,644 --> 00:14:57,980
COMPENSATE.

273
00:14:59,148 --> 00:15:00,817
ORBIT STEADY NOW, SIR.

274
00:15:00,817 --> 00:15:05,154
IT MADE ME A LITTLE NERVOUS,
I GUESS.

275
00:15:05,154 --> 00:15:08,324
THIS SHOULDN'T BE HAPPENING.

276
00:15:09,617 --> 00:15:13,413
THIS MAN
SHOULD BE GETTING STRONGER.

277
00:15:13,413 --> 00:15:15,874
ARE YOU SURE THE RESPIRATOR'S
FUNCTIONING PROPERLY?

278
00:15:15,874 --> 00:15:18,251
YES, DOCTOR.

279
00:15:18,251 --> 00:15:21,295
THEN WHY IS THIS MAN DYING?

280
00:15:24,716 --> 00:15:28,344
HYPO.

281
00:15:30,764 --> 00:15:33,808
[ BREATHING ]

282
00:15:46,738 --> 00:15:50,324
HE'S DEAD, DOCTOR.

283
00:15:50,324 --> 00:15:53,661
THE WOUNDS WERE NOT THAT SEVERE.

284
00:15:57,457 --> 00:15:58,792
[ WHISTLE ]

285
00:15:58,792 --> 00:15:59,667
This is McCoy.

286
00:15:59,667 --> 00:16:02,044
Captain Kirk to sick bay.

287
00:16:02,044 --> 00:16:03,421
UHURA, MONITOR COMMUNICATIONS.

288
00:16:03,421 --> 00:16:04,839
TELL McCOY I'LL BE THERE
WHEN I CAN.

289
00:16:04,839 --> 00:16:06,132
YES, SIR.

290
00:16:06,132 --> 00:16:07,550
PLANET BREAK UP IS IMMINENT,
CAPTAIN,

291
00:16:07,550 --> 00:16:10,553
SHRINKING IN SIZE
AT AN INCREASING RATE.

292
00:16:10,553 --> 00:16:12,889
AS THE PLANET CONTINUES
TO SHRINK IN SIZE,

293
00:16:12,889 --> 00:16:14,933
ITS SURFACE MOVES AWAY FROM US.

294
00:16:14,933 --> 00:16:16,350
FORCING US TO SPIRAL DOWN

295
00:16:16,350 --> 00:16:18,227
TO MAINTAIN
THE SAME DISTANCE FROM IT.

296
00:16:18,227 --> 00:16:19,145
EXACTLY.

297
00:16:19,145 --> 00:16:24,818
WE MUST BE PREPARED TO RESPOND
INSTANTLY TO ANY SUDDEN CHANGE.

298
00:16:24,818 --> 00:16:26,360
ENGINE ROOM FROM BRIDGE.

299
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:27,361
Scott here, Captain.

300
00:16:27,361 --> 00:16:28,529
TIE INTO THE HELM, SCOTTY.

301
00:16:28,529 --> 00:16:30,323
IF WE SHOULD CALL FOR POWER,
WE'LL WANT IT FAST.

302
00:16:30,323 --> 00:16:32,784
No problem, sir.
You'll have it.

303
00:16:32,784 --> 00:16:34,577
RATE OF COMPACTION
SEEMS CONSTANT.

304
00:16:34,577 --> 00:16:36,245
THEN, I'LL GO SEE
WHAT THE GOOD DOCTOR WANTS.

305
00:16:36,245 --> 00:16:38,331
KEEP ME INFORMED OF ANY CHANGE,
MR. SPOCK.

306
00:16:38,331 --> 00:16:41,334
ACKNOWLEDGED.

307
00:16:42,126 --> 00:16:42,877
[ RATTLING SOUND ]

308
00:16:42,877 --> 00:16:48,549
DON'T KNOW IF IT'S THIS PLANET
OR WHAT HAPPENED WITH JOE.

309
00:16:48,549 --> 00:16:50,384
I'M SWEATING LIKE A BRIDEGROOM.

310
00:16:50,384 --> 00:16:51,886
YEAH, ME, TOO.

311
00:16:51,886 --> 00:16:55,014
[ RATTLING SOUND ]

312
00:16:55,014 --> 00:16:56,975
HEY, WHY DON'T YOU COME DOWN
TO THE GYM WITH ME,

313
00:16:56,975 --> 00:16:58,893
KEVIN, M'LAD?

314
00:16:58,893 --> 00:16:59,727
NOW?

315
00:16:59,727 --> 00:17:00,603
WHY NOT?

316
00:17:00,603 --> 00:17:02,563
LIGHT WORKOUT
WILL TAKE THE EDGE OFF.

317
00:17:02,563 --> 00:17:04,941
HEY, SULU, WHAT ABOUT--

318
00:17:04,941 --> 00:17:07,360
HEY, SULU, DON'T BE A FOOL.

319
00:17:07,360 --> 00:17:10,571
COME.

320
00:17:17,328 --> 00:17:22,000
INTESTINAL DAMAGE
WASN'T THAT SEVERE.

321
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:23,417
I GOT TO HIM IN PLENTY OF TIME.

322
00:17:23,417 --> 00:17:26,629
THAT MAN SHOULD STILL BE ALIVE.

323
00:17:26,629 --> 00:17:29,256
ONLY REASON HE DIED, JIM,
IS HE DIDN'T WANT TO LIVE.

324
00:17:29,256 --> 00:17:30,008
HE GAVE UP.

325
00:17:30,008 --> 00:17:31,425
THAT'S A SUPPOSITION, DOCTOR,
NOT A FACT.

326
00:17:31,425 --> 00:17:33,469
WELL, IT MAY BE.
IT MAY BE.

327
00:17:33,469 --> 00:17:36,138
I'VE LOST PATIENTS BEFORE,
BUT NOT LIKE THAT.

328
00:17:36,138 --> 00:17:37,264
NOT JOE'S KIND.

329
00:17:37,264 --> 00:17:41,227
THAT KIND OF MAN
DOESN'T GIVE UP.

330
00:17:43,938 --> 00:17:47,149
COINCIDENCE?

331
00:17:47,149 --> 00:17:49,027
MAYBE.

332
00:17:49,027 --> 00:17:50,737
YOU MEAN THAT JOE WAS DOWN
ON THE PLANET SURFACE,

333
00:17:50,737 --> 00:17:53,031
AND YOU'RE GONNA ASK ME
IF IT'S CONNECTED.

334
00:17:53,031 --> 00:17:55,992
THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT I WAS GONNA ASK.

335
00:17:55,992 --> 00:17:57,952
JIM, HE WAS DECONTAMINATED.

336
00:17:57,952 --> 00:17:59,537
HE'S BEEN MEDICALLY CHECKED.

337
00:17:59,537 --> 00:18:01,789
WE'VE RUN EVERY TEST WE KNOW
FOR EVERYTHING WE KNOW--

338
00:18:01,789 --> 00:18:02,916
THAT'S NOT GOOD ENOUGH.

339
00:18:02,916 --> 00:18:04,500
WELL, WE'RE DOING EVERYTHING
THAT'S POSSIBLE.

340
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:07,587
BONES, I WANT THE IMPOSSIBLE
CHECKED OUT, TOO.

341
00:18:11,716 --> 00:18:15,135
[ BEEPING ]

342
00:18:16,846 --> 00:18:18,305
WHY ISN'T MR. SULU
AT THIS STATION?

343
00:18:18,305 --> 00:18:20,224
MAGNETIC PULL COMPENSATED FOR,
SIR.

344
00:18:20,224 --> 00:18:21,392
ORBIT STEADY.

345
00:18:21,392 --> 00:18:22,268
TAKE OVER HERE, RAND.

346
00:18:22,268 --> 00:18:25,354
YES, SIR.

347
00:18:25,354 --> 00:18:26,731
YOU HAVEN'T ANSWERED
MY QUESTION.

348
00:18:26,731 --> 00:18:28,566
WHERE IS MR. SULU?

349
00:18:28,566 --> 00:18:31,485
HAVE NO FEAR.
RILEY'S HERE.

350
00:18:31,485 --> 00:18:34,113
AND ONE IRISHMAN
IS WORTH 10,000 OF YOU--

351
00:18:34,113 --> 00:18:35,322
YOU'RE RELIEVED, MR. RILEY.

352
00:18:35,322 --> 00:18:37,241
LIEUTENANT UHURA,
TAKE OVER THIS STATION.

353
00:18:37,241 --> 00:18:38,325
YES, SIR.

354
00:18:38,325 --> 00:18:39,994
NOW, THAT'S WHAT I LIKE.

355
00:18:39,994 --> 00:18:41,829
LET THE WOMEN WORK, TOO.

356
00:18:41,829 --> 00:18:43,497
UNIVERSAL SUFFERING.

357
00:18:43,497 --> 00:18:45,083
REPORT TO SICK BAY, MR. RILEY.

358
00:18:45,083 --> 00:18:46,960
SICK BAY?

359
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:52,548
EXACTLY WHERE I WAS HEADED, SIR.

360
00:18:52,548 --> 00:18:54,842
SECURITY, MR. RILEY
IS HEADED FOR SICK BAY.

361
00:18:54,842 --> 00:18:56,844
SEE TO IT HE ARRIVES.

362
00:18:56,844 --> 00:18:59,179
CAPTAIN KIRK TO THE BRIDGE.

363
00:19:35,549 --> 00:19:37,510
WHERE'S JOE?

364
00:19:37,510 --> 00:19:38,511
WELL--

365
00:19:38,511 --> 00:19:41,305
HE DIED, DIDN'T HE?

366
00:19:41,305 --> 00:19:42,932
YES.

367
00:19:42,932 --> 00:19:45,518
YOU KNOW SOMETHING?

368
00:19:45,518 --> 00:19:48,021
YOU HAVE SUCH LOVELY EYES--

369
00:19:48,021 --> 00:19:49,772
[ RATTLING SOUND ]

370
00:19:49,772 --> 00:19:54,318
--PRETTY LADY.

371
00:19:54,318 --> 00:19:59,448
I KNOW HE WAS A FRIEND OF YOURS.
THIS MUST BE A TERRIBLE SHOCK.

372
00:20:00,533 --> 00:20:04,286
YOU KNOW WHAT JOE'S MISTAKE WAS?

373
00:20:04,286 --> 00:20:07,498
HE WASN'T BORN AN IRISHMAN.

374
00:20:29,854 --> 00:20:31,480
[ MUSIC ]

375
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:34,358
RICHELIEU, BEWARE!

376
00:21:00,342 --> 00:21:02,428
STAND.

377
00:21:02,428 --> 00:21:05,806
NO FARTHER.

378
00:21:05,806 --> 00:21:09,309
[ CHUCKLES ]

379
00:21:09,309 --> 00:21:11,270
NO ESCAPE FOR YOU.

380
00:21:11,270 --> 00:21:14,398
YOU EITHER LEAVE THIS BOIS
BLOODIED,

381
00:21:14,398 --> 00:21:18,861
OR WITH MY BLOOD ON YOUR SWORDS.

382
00:21:21,488 --> 00:21:24,909
[ LAUGHS MANIACALLY ]

383
00:21:25,868 --> 00:21:28,121
COWARDS!

384
00:21:28,121 --> 00:21:29,705
LIEUTENANT BRENT,
RELIEVE MS. UHURA.

385
00:21:29,705 --> 00:21:34,001
YES, SIR.

386
00:21:34,001 --> 00:21:35,502
WHAT WERE THEIR SYMPTOMS?

387
00:21:35,502 --> 00:21:37,463
NONVIOLENT AT THIS STAGE.

388
00:21:37,463 --> 00:21:38,839
SLIGHTLY DISORIENTED.

389
00:21:38,839 --> 00:21:41,300
RILEY SEEMED RATHER PLEASED
WITH HIMSELF, AS IF HE WERE--

390
00:21:41,300 --> 00:21:44,762
IRRATIONAL OR DRUGGED.

391
00:21:44,762 --> 00:21:46,305
PRECISELY.

392
00:21:46,305 --> 00:21:47,890
SECURITY, LIEUTENANT UHURA.

393
00:21:47,890 --> 00:21:48,432
YES, SIR.

394
00:21:48,432 --> 00:21:50,726
BOTH SULU AND RILEY,
LOCATE AND CONFINE.

395
00:21:50,726 --> 00:21:52,270
I WANT EVERY CREWMAN
WHO COMES IN CONTACT WITH THEM

396
00:21:52,270 --> 00:21:53,271
MEDICALLY CHECKED.

397
00:21:53,271 --> 00:21:57,524
SIR, LEVEL TWO, CORRIDOR THREE
REPORTS A DISTURBANCE:

398
00:21:57,524 --> 00:22:03,114
MR. SULU CHASING CREWMEN
WITH A SWORD.

399
00:22:03,114 --> 00:22:04,531
PUT SECURITY ON IT.

400
00:22:04,531 --> 00:22:06,951
FASCINATING.
A PATTERN IS DEVELOPING.

401
00:22:06,951 --> 00:22:08,327
FIRST, TORMOLEN.

402
00:22:08,327 --> 00:22:11,664
HIDDEN PERSONALITY TRAITS
BEING FORCED TO THE SURFACE.

403
00:22:11,664 --> 00:22:15,375
THEN RILEY, WHO FANCIES HIMSELF
A DESCENDANT OF IRISH KINGS.

404
00:22:15,375 --> 00:22:18,420
AND NOW, SULU,
WHO IS AT HEART A SWASHBUCKLER

405
00:22:18,420 --> 00:22:19,797
OUT OF YOUR 18th CENTURY.

406
00:22:19,797 --> 00:22:21,924
[ BEEPING ]

407
00:22:21,924 --> 00:22:23,550
PRESENT CONDITION OF PSI 2000.

408
00:22:23,550 --> 00:22:24,551
GRAVITY PULL INCREASING.

409
00:22:24,551 --> 00:22:26,012
WE'VE SHIFTED TO 2%
AND SHOULD STABILIZE

410
00:22:26,012 --> 00:22:26,887
OUR POSITION.

411
00:22:26,887 --> 00:22:28,472
HELMSMAN, STABILIZE POSITION.

412
00:22:28,472 --> 00:22:31,225
HELM IS NOT ANSWERING
TO CONTROL.

413
00:22:31,225 --> 00:22:32,559
WARP US OUT OF HERE.

414
00:22:32,559 --> 00:22:33,477
NO RESPONSE FROM ENGINES, SIR.

415
00:22:33,477 --> 00:22:35,729
IMPULSE POWER THEN.
BLAST US OUT OF THIS ORBIT.

416
00:22:35,729 --> 00:22:37,857
IMPULSE ENGINES ALSO DEAD, SIR.

417
00:22:37,857 --> 00:22:41,359
ENGINE ROOM, WE NEED POWER!

418
00:22:41,359 --> 00:22:43,237
MR. SCOTT, ACKNOWLEDGE.

419
00:22:43,237 --> 00:22:46,699
OUR CONTROLS ARE DEAD.

420
00:22:46,699 --> 00:22:49,493
TAKE HER.

421
00:22:50,244 --> 00:22:52,079
RICHELIEU, AT LAST.

422
00:22:52,079 --> 00:22:54,414
SULU, PUT THAT--
PUT THAT THING AWAY.

423
00:22:54,414 --> 00:22:59,419
FOR HONOR, QUEEN, AND FRANCE!

424
00:23:01,297 --> 00:23:04,466
[ LAUGHS ]

425
00:23:04,466 --> 00:23:07,261
[ SWISHING ]

426
00:23:09,180 --> 00:23:10,514
SULU.

427
00:23:10,514 --> 00:23:13,142
AH.

428
00:23:13,142 --> 00:23:16,394
SULU, GIVE ME THAT.

429
00:23:16,394 --> 00:23:18,356
I'LL PROTECT YOU, FAIR MAIDEN.

430
00:23:18,356 --> 00:23:20,316
SORRY, NEITHER.

431
00:23:20,316 --> 00:23:23,819
FOUL RICHELIEU.

432
00:23:28,699 --> 00:23:30,159
I'D LIKE YOU
TO TEACH ME THAT SOMETIME.

433
00:23:30,159 --> 00:23:32,161
TAKE D'ARTAGNON HERE TO SICKBAY.

434
00:23:32,161 --> 00:23:34,872
SCOTTY, WE NEED POWER.

435
00:23:34,872 --> 00:23:36,707
ENGINE ROOM, ACKNOWLEDGE!

436
00:23:36,707 --> 00:23:38,667
You rang, sir?

437
00:23:38,667 --> 00:23:39,417
WHO'S THIS?

438
00:23:39,417 --> 00:23:42,129
THIS IS CAPTAIN KEVIN
THOMAS RILEY

439
00:23:42,129 --> 00:23:44,215
OF THE STARSHIP<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

440
00:23:44,215 --> 00:23:45,507
And who is this?

441
00:23:45,507 --> 00:23:46,300
THIS IS CAPTAIN KIRK.

442
00:23:46,300 --> 00:23:47,385
GET OUT OF THE ENGINE ROOM,
NAVIGATOR.

443
00:23:47,385 --> 00:23:48,426
WHERE'S MR. SCOTT?

444
00:23:48,426 --> 00:23:52,681
I've relieved
Mr. Scott of his duties.

445
00:23:52,681 --> 00:23:54,558
Now, attention cooks.

446
00:23:54,558 --> 00:23:57,311
This is your captain speaking.

447
00:23:57,311 --> 00:24:00,731
I would like double
portions of ice cream

448
00:24:00,731 --> 00:24:02,900
for the entire crew.

449
00:24:02,900 --> 00:24:04,110
CLEAR THAT TUBE, WILL YOU?

450
00:24:04,110 --> 00:24:05,069
YES, SIR.

451
00:24:05,069 --> 00:24:07,988
And now,
your captain will render

452
00:24:07,988 --> 00:24:10,616
an ancient Irish favorite.

453
00:24:10,616 --> 00:24:13,411
♪ I'll take you home
again Kathleen... ♪

454
00:24:13,411 --> 00:24:15,829
CAPTAIN, AT OUR PRESENT
RATE OF DESCENT,

455
00:24:15,829 --> 00:24:17,415
WE HAVE LESS THAN 20 MINUTES
BEFORE WE ENTER

456
00:24:17,415 --> 00:24:18,958
PLANET ATMOSPHERE.

457
00:24:18,958 --> 00:24:20,751
AND BURN UP. I KNOW, MR. SPOCK.

458
00:24:20,751 --> 00:24:27,507
♪ Wild and wide
to where your heart... ♪

459
00:24:31,929 --> 00:24:34,932
CAPTAIN'S LOG, STARDATE 1704.4.

460
00:24:34,932 --> 00:24:36,016
SHIP OUT OF CONTROL,

461
00:24:36,016 --> 00:24:39,019
SPIRALING DOWN
TOWARDS PLANET PSI 2000.

462
00:24:39,019 --> 00:24:42,148
WE HAVE 19 MINUTES OF LIFE LEFT
WITHOUT ENGINE POWER

463
00:24:42,148 --> 00:24:44,358
OR HELM CONTROL.

464
00:24:44,358 --> 00:24:45,276
HOW DID RILEY GET IN THERE?

465
00:24:45,276 --> 00:24:46,902
HE RAN IN, SAID YOU WANTED US
ON THE BRIDGE.

466
00:24:46,902 --> 00:24:48,362
HE'S CUT OFF
BOTH HELM AND POWER.

467
00:24:48,362 --> 00:24:50,197
AND HE SHUT THE DOOR BEHIND US
AND LOCKED OFF THE MECHANISM.

468
00:24:50,197 --> 00:24:51,615
CAN'T YOU GET
TO THE AUXILIARY?

469
00:24:51,615 --> 00:24:52,283
I CAN'T.

470
00:24:52,283 --> 00:24:54,201
HE'S HOOKED EVERYTHING
THROUGH THE MAIN PANEL IN THERE.

471
00:24:54,201 --> 00:24:55,328
GET UP TO MY OFFICE
AND PULL THE PLANS

472
00:24:55,328 --> 00:24:57,830
FOR THIS BULKHEAD.

473
00:24:57,830 --> 00:24:59,832
THE ONLY WAY
TO GET THAT DOOR OPEN

474
00:24:59,832 --> 00:25:04,586
IS TO CUT THROUGH
THESE WALL CIRCUITS HERE.

475
00:25:04,586 --> 00:25:10,259
♪ THE ROSES
ALL HAVE LEFT YOUR CHEEKS ♪

476
00:25:10,259 --> 00:25:16,140
♪ I'VE WATCHED THEM
FADE AWAY AND DIE ♪

477
00:25:16,140 --> 00:25:17,850
STATUS REPORTS, ALL SECTIONS.

478
00:25:17,850 --> 00:25:19,726
MR. SPOCK,
A FIGHT IN THE AFT WARDROOM.

479
00:25:19,726 --> 00:25:21,561
SECURITY REPORTS INCIDENTS
AMONG THE CREWMEN

480
00:25:21,561 --> 00:25:23,022
ARE INCREASING.

481
00:25:23,022 --> 00:25:24,273
GO TO ALERT BAKER TWO.

482
00:25:24,273 --> 00:25:26,317
SEAL OFF MAIN SECTIONS.

483
00:25:26,317 --> 00:25:29,028
ALL DECKS, ALERT SYSTEM B TWO.

484
00:25:29,028 --> 00:25:32,448
REPEAT,
GO TO ALERT CONDITION BAKER TWO.

485
00:25:32,448 --> 00:25:34,492
SEAL OFF ALL MAIN SECTIONS.

486
00:25:34,492 --> 00:25:35,575
STAND BY.

487
00:25:35,575 --> 00:25:36,660
SEAL OFF, CAPTAIN,

488
00:25:36,660 --> 00:25:39,372
IF WE CAN MINIMIZE THE SPREAD
OF WHATEVER THIS IS.

489
00:25:39,372 --> 00:25:40,580
CONTINUE THE ALERT, LIEUTENANT.

490
00:25:40,580 --> 00:25:41,707
I CAN'T, SIR.

491
00:25:41,707 --> 00:25:44,335
HE'S CUT OFF THE ALERT CHANNELS.

492
00:25:44,335 --> 00:25:48,714
LIEUTENANT UHURA,
YOU'VE INTERRUPTED MY SONG.

493
00:25:48,714 --> 00:25:53,469
I'm sorry, but there'll be
no ice cream for you tonight.

494
00:25:53,469 --> 00:25:54,345
CUT HIM OFF.

495
00:25:54,345 --> 00:25:55,553
I CAN'T, SIR.

496
00:25:55,553 --> 00:25:56,930
THERE'S NO WAY TO DO IT.

497
00:25:56,930 --> 00:25:58,140
Attention, crew.

498
00:25:58,140 --> 00:26:00,309
This is Captain Riley.

499
00:26:00,309 --> 00:26:05,272
There will be a formal dance
in the bowling alley

500
00:26:05,272 --> 00:26:07,607
at 1900 hours tonight.

501
00:26:07,607 --> 00:26:08,359
NO WAY, CAPTAIN.

502
00:26:08,359 --> 00:26:09,902
HE CONTROLS
THE MAIN POWER PANELS.

503
00:26:09,902 --> 00:26:12,488
HE CAN OVERRIDE ANY CHANNEL
FROM DOWN THERE.

504
00:26:12,488 --> 00:26:13,906
17 MINUTES LEFT, SIR.

505
00:26:13,906 --> 00:26:17,659
[ MUSIC ]

506
00:26:26,252 --> 00:26:30,297
Sick bay to bridge.

507
00:26:30,297 --> 00:26:31,549
CAN YOU TIE ME IN
TO THE SICK BAY?

508
00:26:31,549 --> 00:26:32,841
I'M GETTING YOU, JIM.

509
00:26:32,841 --> 00:26:34,552
LOOK,
CAN YOU KEEP THIS BEAST LEVEL?

510
00:26:34,552 --> 00:26:35,886
I'VE GOT SULU TRANQUILIZED.

511
00:26:35,886 --> 00:26:37,471
WE'RE RUNNING TESTS ON HIM.

512
00:26:37,471 --> 00:26:39,723
So far there's nothing unusual
in his bloodstream.

513
00:26:39,723 --> 00:26:41,850
Body functions seem normal.

514
00:26:41,850 --> 00:26:43,852
RILEY'S THE IMMEDIATE PROBLEM,
DOCTOR.

515
00:26:43,852 --> 00:26:45,854
IS THERE ANY WAY,
ANYTHING YOU CAN DO

516
00:26:45,854 --> 00:26:47,189
TO SNAP HIM OUT OF IT?

517
00:26:47,189 --> 00:26:49,607
NEGATIVE, UNTIL I CAN GET
A LITTLE FARTHER ON THESE TESTS.

518
00:26:49,607 --> 00:26:51,151
This is Captain Riley.

519
00:26:51,151 --> 00:26:53,195
Crew,
I have some additional orders.

520
00:26:53,195 --> 00:26:56,698
IN THE FUTURE,
ALL FEMALE CREW MEMBERS

521
00:26:56,698 --> 00:27:02,162
WILL WEAR THEIR HAIR LOOSELY,
ABOUT THEIR SHOULDERS.

522
00:27:02,162 --> 00:27:04,540
And use restraint
in putting on your makeup.

523
00:27:04,540 --> 00:27:08,626
Women,
women should not look made up.

524
00:27:08,626 --> 00:27:12,839
And now, crew,
I will render Kathleen,

525
00:27:12,839 --> 00:27:15,884
one more time!

526
00:27:15,884 --> 00:27:18,095
PLEASE, NOT AGAIN.

527
00:27:18,095 --> 00:27:23,850
♪ I'LL TAKE YOU HOME AGAIN,
KATHLEEN... ♪

528
00:27:50,085 --> 00:27:55,382
♪ I'VE WATCHED THEM
FADE AWAY AND DIE ♪

529
00:27:57,343 --> 00:27:58,260
I'VE SET THE JUMPERS UP THERE.

530
00:27:58,260 --> 00:28:02,473
STANDBY
TILL I GIVE YOU A SIGNAL.

531
00:28:02,473 --> 00:28:09,229
♪ AND TEARS BEDIM
YOUR LOVING EYES, OH ♪

532
00:28:12,566 --> 00:28:13,775
ENGINEERING TO BRIDGE.

533
00:28:13,775 --> 00:28:14,401
TRY YOUR HELM.

534
00:28:14,401 --> 00:28:17,112
YOU'LL HAVE ENOUGH POWER
TO KEEP HER STABILIZED.

535
00:28:17,112 --> 00:28:19,906
HERE, LET'S HAVE A LOOK AT THAT.

536
00:28:23,494 --> 00:28:26,580
[ BEEPING ]

537
00:28:29,208 --> 00:28:30,376
16 MINUTES LEFT, CAPTAIN.

538
00:28:30,376 --> 00:28:32,628
WE'VE STABILIZED,
BUT STILL SPIRALING DOWN.

539
00:28:32,628 --> 00:28:33,837
EMERGENCY SIGNAL, CAPTAIN.

540
00:28:33,837 --> 00:28:35,381
BOTH DECKS FOUR AND FIVE.

541
00:28:35,381 --> 00:28:37,007
FIGHTS AND DISORDERS.

542
00:28:37,007 --> 00:28:38,217
GET ME SICK BAY.

543
00:28:38,217 --> 00:28:39,677
I HAVE NO INTERCOM FOR SICK BAY.

544
00:28:39,677 --> 00:28:40,886
HE KEEPS SWITCHING
CHANNELS ON ME.

545
00:28:40,886 --> 00:28:42,762
SEE WHAT YOU CAN DO
TO HELP DOCTOR McCOY.

546
00:28:42,762 --> 00:28:43,763
BETTER CHECK SCOTTY FIRST.

547
00:28:43,763 --> 00:28:44,390
MOVE HIM FASTER.

548
00:28:44,390 --> 00:28:47,393
HE'S GOT TO GET THROUGH
THAT BULKHEAD.

549
00:28:51,146 --> 00:28:54,733
[ LAUGHS MANIACALLY ]

550
00:29:00,573 --> 00:29:03,325
CREWMAN, REPORT TO THE LAB!

551
00:29:07,829 --> 00:29:11,833
♪ I'LL TAKE YOU HOME AGAIN,
JAN... ♪

552
00:29:11,833 --> 00:29:13,168
WHAT'S GOING ON?

553
00:29:13,168 --> 00:29:14,503
MR. SPOCK,
I'M TRYING TO GET TO THE BRIDGE

554
00:29:14,503 --> 00:29:16,046
AND THIS CREWMAN
WON'T LET ME BY.

555
00:29:16,046 --> 00:29:17,256
CREWMAN, STAND ASIDE.

556
00:29:17,256 --> 00:29:20,426
OH, YES, SIR.

557
00:29:20,426 --> 00:29:23,721
♪ I'LL TAKE YOU HOME AGAIN,
JANICE ♪

558
00:29:23,721 --> 00:29:27,015
SPOCK!

559
00:29:36,191 --> 00:29:37,359
MESSAGE FROM THE CAPTAIN.

560
00:29:37,359 --> 00:29:38,569
TELL HIM I'M DOING MY BEST.

561
00:29:38,569 --> 00:29:39,612
IF I CUT
THROUGH THE WRONG CIRCUITS--

562
00:29:39,612 --> 00:29:41,572
WE HAVE 14 MINUTES LEFT.

563
00:29:41,572 --> 00:29:43,156
EVEN IF WE ARE
UNDER A FULL-SCALE ATTACK,

564
00:29:43,156 --> 00:29:45,075
I COULDN'T MOVE ANY FASTER,
NOT AND MAINTAIN

565
00:29:45,075 --> 00:29:46,118
A SAFETY FACTOR.

566
00:29:46,118 --> 00:29:47,911
AT THE RATE YOU'RE PROCEEDING,
CALCULATIONS SHOW

567
00:29:47,911 --> 00:29:49,580
THAT YOU'LL TAKE
A MINUTE AND A HALF

568
00:29:49,580 --> 00:29:50,956
MORE THAN WE HAVE LEFT.

569
00:29:50,956 --> 00:29:52,958
YOU CAN'T AFFORD
A SAFETY FACTOR.

570
00:29:52,958 --> 00:29:56,503
[ MUSIC ]

571
00:30:10,643 --> 00:30:12,978
BIOPSY LAB.

572
00:30:12,978 --> 00:30:17,190
BIOPSY, WHERE'S MY REPORT?

573
00:30:17,190 --> 00:30:20,360
BIOPSY, COME IN.

574
00:30:20,360 --> 00:30:24,573
HARRISON, WHERE'S MY REPORT?

575
00:30:24,573 --> 00:30:25,699
I'M GOING TO THE LAB.

576
00:30:25,699 --> 00:30:26,575
SIR?

577
00:30:26,575 --> 00:30:27,618
YEAH?

578
00:30:27,618 --> 00:30:29,369
THE TRANQUILIZER'S WEARING OFF.

579
00:30:29,369 --> 00:30:30,579
OH, GOOD.
I'LL NEED HIM CONSCIOUS NOW.

580
00:30:30,579 --> 00:30:33,540
CONTINUE TO EXAMINE HIM
ON CIRCUITS K ONE AND THREE.

581
00:30:33,540 --> 00:30:36,627
OF COURSE, DOCTOR.

582
00:30:46,928 --> 00:30:50,223
[ GRUNTING ]

583
00:30:59,983 --> 00:31:03,069
[ RATTLING SOUND ]

584
00:31:12,329 --> 00:31:14,331
[ GRUNTING ]

585
00:31:14,331 --> 00:31:18,627
[ LAUGHS ]

586
00:31:18,627 --> 00:31:19,961
GET HIM OUT OF HERE.

587
00:31:19,961 --> 00:31:22,589
♪ I'll take you-- ♪

588
00:31:22,589 --> 00:31:23,423
I WOULD'VE GOTTEN HERE SOONER,
SIR.

589
00:31:23,423 --> 00:31:24,424
BUT CREWMAN MOODY STOPPED ME
IN THE HALL--

590
00:31:24,424 --> 00:31:25,300
- TAKE THE HELM.
- SIR?

591
00:31:25,300 --> 00:31:30,013
- TAKE THE HELM.
- YES, SIR.

592
00:31:30,013 --> 00:31:33,183
And now, crew, one more time--

593
00:31:33,183 --> 00:31:34,100
PLEASE TRY AND CUT HIM OFF.

594
00:31:34,100 --> 00:31:36,603
SIR, IF I COULD CUT HIM OFF,
DON'T YOU THINK I--

595
00:31:36,603 --> 00:31:39,356
♪ I'll take you home again,
Kathleen-- ♪

596
00:31:39,356 --> 00:31:42,776
YES, SIR. I'LL KEEP TRYING.

597
00:31:42,776 --> 00:31:43,527
SORRY.

598
00:31:43,527 --> 00:31:49,533
♪ Across the ocean
wild and wide ♪

599
00:31:49,533 --> 00:31:51,201
- SCOTTY?
- Engine room.

600
00:31:51,201 --> 00:31:52,452
WE'VE GOT 12 MINUTES LEFT.

601
00:31:52,452 --> 00:31:53,704
IT'LL TAKE AT LEAST
TWO OR THREE OF THEM

602
00:31:53,704 --> 00:31:55,038
TO GET THE ENGINES
UP TO POWER NOW.

603
00:31:55,038 --> 00:31:57,750
Then we'll make it, sir,
if all goes right.

604
00:31:57,750 --> 00:31:59,292
CALL ME WHEN YOU'VE CUT THROUGH.
I WANT TO BE THERE.

605
00:31:59,292 --> 00:32:00,377
KIRK OUT.

606
00:32:00,377 --> 00:32:03,004
[ MUSIC ]

607
00:32:05,340 --> 00:32:07,593
NURSE?

608
00:32:07,593 --> 00:32:09,595
WHERE IS DR. McCOY?

609
00:32:09,595 --> 00:32:13,181
HE'S GONE TO THE LAB.

610
00:32:16,518 --> 00:32:18,687
LAB?

611
00:32:18,687 --> 00:32:21,481
LAB, RESPOND, PLEASE.
SPOCK HERE.

612
00:32:21,481 --> 00:32:24,025
LAB?

613
00:32:25,652 --> 00:32:26,737
MR. SPOCK?

614
00:32:26,737 --> 00:32:27,487
WHAT IS IT, NURSE?

615
00:32:27,487 --> 00:32:28,363
MR. SPOCK.

616
00:32:28,363 --> 00:32:29,489
[ RATTLING SOUND ]

617
00:32:29,489 --> 00:32:32,785
THE MEN FROM VULCAN
TREAT THEIR WOMEN STRANGELY.

618
00:32:35,913 --> 00:32:40,083
AT LEAST, PEOPLE SAY THAT.

619
00:32:40,083 --> 00:32:43,253
BUT YOU'RE PART HUMAN, TOO.

620
00:32:43,253 --> 00:32:45,046
I KNOW YOU DON'T.

621
00:32:45,046 --> 00:32:49,301
YOU COULDN'T HURT ME.

622
00:32:49,301 --> 00:32:52,304
WOULD YOU?

623
00:33:01,187 --> 00:33:05,066
I'M IN LOVE WITH YOU, MR. SPOCK.

624
00:33:13,784 --> 00:33:21,917
YOU, THE HUMAN MR. SPOCK,
THE VULCAN MR. SPOCK.

625
00:33:23,794 --> 00:33:24,544
NURSE, YOU SHOULD--

626
00:33:24,544 --> 00:33:27,631
CHRISTINE, PLEASE.

627
00:33:27,631 --> 00:33:32,719
I SEE THINGS,
HOW HONEST YOU ARE.

628
00:33:32,719 --> 00:33:35,180
I KNOW HOW YOU FEEL.

629
00:33:35,180 --> 00:33:39,810
YOU HIDE IT,
BUT YOU DO HAVE FEELING.

630
00:33:39,810 --> 00:33:45,106
OH, HOW WE MUST HURT YOU,
TORTURE YOU.

631
00:33:45,106 --> 00:33:48,401
I'M IN CONTROL OF MY EMOTIONS.

632
00:33:48,401 --> 00:33:49,736
THE OTHERS BELIEVE THAT.

633
00:33:49,736 --> 00:33:52,531
I DON'T.

634
00:33:52,531 --> 00:33:55,241
I LOVE YOU.

635
00:33:55,241 --> 00:33:56,827
I DON'T KNOW WHY,
BUT I LOVE YOU.

636
00:33:56,827 --> 00:34:02,499
I DO LOVE YOU JUST AS YOU ARE.

637
00:34:02,499 --> 00:34:05,418
OH, I LOVE YOU.

638
00:34:05,418 --> 00:34:06,003
I'M SORRY--

639
00:34:06,003 --> 00:34:08,129
Captain is en route engineering,
Mr. Spock.

640
00:34:08,129 --> 00:34:09,172
Can you take the bridge?

641
00:34:09,172 --> 00:34:12,801
Acknowledge.

642
00:34:12,801 --> 00:34:15,136
I AM SORRY.

643
00:34:15,136 --> 00:34:18,264
CHRISTINE.

644
00:34:19,808 --> 00:34:21,226
CHRISTINE.

645
00:34:21,226 --> 00:34:22,686
[ WHISTLING ]

646
00:34:22,686 --> 00:34:24,103
Bridge to sick bay.

647
00:34:24,103 --> 00:34:28,066
Is Mr. Spock there?

648
00:34:42,330 --> 00:34:44,499
[ WHISTLING ]

649
00:34:44,499 --> 00:34:47,252
Mr. Spock,
would you please acknowledge?

650
00:35:18,533 --> 00:35:23,246
♪ I will take you home,
Kathleen ♪

651
00:35:23,246 --> 00:35:24,414
ALMOST READY, SIR.

652
00:35:24,414 --> 00:35:31,964
♪ To where your heart
will feel no pain ♪

653
00:35:31,964 --> 00:35:39,096
♪ When the fields
are fresh and green ♪

654
00:35:39,096 --> 00:35:43,767
♪ I'll take you to your home-- ♪

655
00:35:43,767 --> 00:35:44,643
READY, SIR?

656
00:35:44,643 --> 00:35:46,352
FOLLOW ME THROUGH.

657
00:35:46,352 --> 00:35:47,395
PUT YOUR PHASERS ON STUN.

658
00:35:47,395 --> 00:35:50,523
DON'T FIRE UNLESS HE'S ARMED.
GO.

659
00:35:50,523 --> 00:35:52,275
[ MUSIC ]

660
00:35:52,275 --> 00:35:54,152
♪ I'LL TAKE-- ♪

661
00:35:54,152 --> 00:35:56,571
NO DANCE TONIGHT.

662
00:35:56,571 --> 00:35:59,825
GET HIM OUT OF HERE.

663
00:35:59,825 --> 00:36:04,245
[ BEEPING ]

664
00:36:06,331 --> 00:36:10,127
[ CRYING ]

665
00:36:23,807 --> 00:36:28,020
I'M IN CONTROL OF MY EMOTIONS.

666
00:36:28,020 --> 00:36:32,149
IN CONTROL OF MY EMOTIONS.

667
00:36:35,652 --> 00:36:42,075
I'M AN OFFICER. AN OFFICER.

668
00:36:47,831 --> 00:36:50,125
MY DUTY.

669
00:36:50,125 --> 00:36:53,837
MY DUTY IS--

670
00:37:11,021 --> 00:37:14,315
MY DUTY IS TO--

671
00:37:17,694 --> 00:37:21,531
TOO LATE.

672
00:37:21,531 --> 00:37:25,368
I'M SORRY.

673
00:37:27,162 --> 00:37:33,085
TWO--TWO, FOUR, SIX--
SIX--SIX TIMES--SIX TIMES.

674
00:37:45,055 --> 00:37:46,973
[ CRYING ]

675
00:37:46,973 --> 00:37:51,644
SIX TIMES.

676
00:37:55,190 --> 00:37:56,108
[ BEEPING ]

677
00:37:56,108 --> 00:37:57,692
SCOTTY,
WE HAVEN'T GOT MUCH TIME LEFT.

678
00:37:57,692 --> 00:38:02,030
Bridge to Captain.

679
00:38:02,030 --> 00:38:02,948
KIRK HERE.

680
00:38:02,948 --> 00:38:05,450
Entering
planet's outer atmosphere, sir.

681
00:38:05,450 --> 00:38:06,952
CAPTAIN?

682
00:38:06,952 --> 00:38:07,953
WHAT IS IT?

683
00:38:07,953 --> 00:38:11,497
HE'S TURNED THE ENGINES OFF,
COMPLETELY COLD.

684
00:38:11,497 --> 00:38:13,208
IT'LL TAKE 30 MINUTES
TO REGENERATE THEM.

685
00:38:13,208 --> 00:38:15,794
Ship's outer skin
is beginning to heat, Captain.

686
00:38:15,794 --> 00:38:18,463
Orbit plat shows we have
about eight minutes left.

687
00:38:18,463 --> 00:38:19,214
SCOTTY?

688
00:38:19,214 --> 00:38:22,092
I CAN'T CHANGE
THE LAWS OF PHYSICS.

689
00:38:22,092 --> 00:38:25,011
I GOT TO HAVE 30 MINUTES.

690
00:38:25,011 --> 00:38:28,098
[ MUSIC ]

691
00:38:35,480 --> 00:38:37,149
CAPTAIN'S LOG, SUPPLEMENTAL.

692
00:38:37,149 --> 00:38:39,525
THE<i> ENTERPRISE</i>
SPIRALING DOWN OUT OF CONTROL.

693
00:38:39,525 --> 00:38:41,360
SHIP'S OUTER SKIN
HEATING RAPIDLY

694
00:38:41,360 --> 00:38:43,738
DUE TO FRICTION
WITH PLANET ATMOSPHERE.

695
00:38:43,738 --> 00:38:45,115
MAYBE 22, 23 MINUTES--

696
00:38:45,115 --> 00:38:46,616
SCOTTY, WE'VE GOT SIX.

697
00:38:46,616 --> 00:38:51,204
CAPTAIN, YOU CAN'T MIX
MATTER AND ANTIMATTER COLD.

698
00:38:51,204 --> 00:38:52,914
WE'D GO UP
IN THE BIGGEST EXPLOSION SINCE--

699
00:38:52,914 --> 00:38:55,959
WE CAN BALANCE OUR ENGINES
INTO A CONTROLLED IMPLOSION.

700
00:38:55,959 --> 00:38:57,002
THAT'S ONLY A THEORY.

701
00:38:57,002 --> 00:38:59,671
IT'S NEVER BEEN DONE.

702
00:38:59,671 --> 00:39:02,048
BRIDGE,
HAVE YOU FOUND MR. SPOCK YET?

703
00:39:02,048 --> 00:39:03,883
IF YOU WANTED A CHANCE,
ODDS OF 10 THOUSAND TO 1,

704
00:39:03,883 --> 00:39:05,635
MAYBE, ASSUMING
WE HAD A ROW OF COMPUTERS

705
00:39:05,635 --> 00:39:07,720
WORKING WEEKS
ON THE RIGHT FORMULA.

706
00:39:07,720 --> 00:39:09,848
Mr. Spock is not on the bridge,
Captain.

707
00:39:09,848 --> 00:39:13,226
[ SCREAMING ]

708
00:39:19,024 --> 00:39:22,944
I WAS ON THE BRIDGE.

709
00:39:24,487 --> 00:39:29,367
HEY, DOC, WHAT AM I DOING HERE?

710
00:39:31,786 --> 00:39:34,580
McCOY TO BIO. WE'VE ISOLATED IT.
START PREPARING SERUM.

711
00:39:34,580 --> 00:39:35,707
What, Doctor?

712
00:39:35,707 --> 00:39:36,499
[ LAUGHS ]

713
00:39:36,499 --> 00:39:37,292
IT'S WATER.

714
00:39:37,292 --> 00:39:38,376
SOMEHOW ON THIS PLANET,
WATER'S CHANGED

715
00:39:38,376 --> 00:39:40,086
TO A COMPLEX CHAIN OF MOLECULES.

716
00:39:40,086 --> 00:39:41,838
What's that, Doctor?

717
00:39:41,838 --> 00:39:42,630
THAT'S HOW WE MISSED IT.

718
00:39:42,630 --> 00:39:44,757
IT PASSED FROM MAN TO MAN
THROUGH PERSPIRATION.

719
00:39:44,757 --> 00:39:46,759
ONCE IN THE BLOODSTREAM,
IT ACTS LIKE ALCOHOL,

720
00:39:46,759 --> 00:39:48,136
DEPRESSES
THE CENTERS OF JUDGMENT,

721
00:39:48,136 --> 00:39:49,137
SELF-CONTROL.

722
00:39:49,137 --> 00:39:50,347
NOW, GET SOMEONE TO THE LAB.

723
00:39:50,347 --> 00:39:53,058
TELL THEM THE SERUM WORKS,
AND START PREPARING MORE.

724
00:39:53,058 --> 00:39:56,228
[ LAUGHS ]

725
00:39:56,228 --> 00:39:58,063
DOC,
WILL YOU LET ME OUT OF HERE?

726
00:39:58,063 --> 00:39:59,314
-I'M ALL RIGHT.
-[ SNAPPING ]

727
00:39:59,314 --> 00:40:00,899
RELEASE HIM.

728
00:40:00,899 --> 00:40:02,400
[ WHISTLING ]

729
00:40:02,400 --> 00:40:04,319
Engineers, man your stations.

730
00:40:04,319 --> 00:40:05,653
Engine rooms, report.

731
00:40:05,653 --> 00:40:07,239
Cycling station, report.

732
00:40:07,239 --> 00:40:10,158
This will be an emergency
restart of engines.

733
00:40:10,158 --> 00:40:11,326
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?
WHAT HAPPENED?

734
00:40:11,326 --> 00:40:12,952
MY MOTHER.

735
00:40:12,952 --> 00:40:15,288
I COULD NEVER TELL HER
I LOVED HER.

736
00:40:15,288 --> 00:40:17,665
WE'VE GOT FOUR MINUTES,
MAYBE FIVE.

737
00:40:17,665 --> 00:40:20,168
AN EARTH WOMAN,
LIVING ON A PLANET

738
00:40:20,168 --> 00:40:25,090
WHERE LOVE, EMOTION,
IS BAD TASTE.

739
00:40:25,090 --> 00:40:26,799
WE'VE GOT TO RISK
A FULL-POWER START.

740
00:40:26,799 --> 00:40:27,842
THE ENGINES WERE SHUT OFF.

741
00:40:27,842 --> 00:40:29,052
NO TIME TO REGENERATE THEM.

742
00:40:29,052 --> 00:40:29,761
DO YOU HEAR ME?

743
00:40:29,761 --> 00:40:32,180
WE'VE GOT TO RISK
A FULL POWER START!

744
00:40:32,180 --> 00:40:34,349
I RESPECTED MY FATHER,
OUR CUSTOMS.

745
00:40:34,349 --> 00:40:38,644
I WAS ASHAMED OF MY EARTH BLOOD.

746
00:40:38,644 --> 00:40:43,316
JIM,
WHEN I FEEL FRIENDSHIP FOR YOU,

747
00:40:43,316 --> 00:40:44,609
I'M ASHAMED.

748
00:40:44,609 --> 00:40:48,154
YOU'VE GOT TO HEAR ME!

749
00:40:48,154 --> 00:40:49,364
WE NEED A FORMULA!

750
00:40:49,364 --> 00:40:50,907
WE'VE GOT TO RISK IMPLOSION!

751
00:40:50,907 --> 00:40:54,327
NEVER BEEN DONE!

752
00:40:55,578 --> 00:40:57,997
UNDERSTAND, JIM?

753
00:40:57,997 --> 00:41:02,919
I'VE SPENT A WHOLE LIFETIME
LEARNING TO HIDE MY FEELINGS.

754
00:41:11,261 --> 00:41:14,097
WE'VE GOT TO RISK IMPLOSION.
IT'S OUR ONLY CHANCE.

755
00:41:14,097 --> 00:41:15,473
IT'S NEVER BEEN DONE.

756
00:41:15,473 --> 00:41:17,016
DON'T TELL ME THAT AGAIN,
SCIENCE OFFICER!

757
00:41:17,016 --> 00:41:18,726
IT'S A THEORY! IT'S POSSIBLE!

758
00:41:18,726 --> 00:41:20,103
WE MAY GO UP
INTO THE BIGGEST BALL OF FIRE

759
00:41:20,103 --> 00:41:21,896
SINCE THE LAST SUN
ON THESE PARTS EXPLODED,

760
00:41:21,896 --> 00:41:23,940
BUT WE'VE GOT TO
TAKE THAT 1 IN 10,000 CHANCE!

761
00:41:23,940 --> 00:41:25,108
Bridge to Captain.

762
00:41:25,108 --> 00:41:26,776
Engineer asked, did you find--

763
00:41:26,776 --> 00:41:28,278
YES, I FOUND MR. SPOCK!

764
00:41:28,278 --> 00:41:30,280
I'M TALKING TO MR. SPOCK,
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

765
00:41:30,280 --> 00:41:31,197
Yes, sir.

766
00:41:31,197 --> 00:41:32,740
Three and a half minutes left,
Captain.

767
00:41:32,740 --> 00:41:37,370
I'VE GOT IT, THE DISEASE.

768
00:41:40,832 --> 00:41:42,834
LOVE.

769
00:41:42,834 --> 00:41:47,964
YOU'RE BETTER OFF WITHOUT IT,
AND I'M BETTER OFF WITHOUT MINE.

770
00:41:47,964 --> 00:41:51,717
THIS VESSEL,

771
00:41:51,717 --> 00:41:55,763
I GIVE, SHE TAKES.

772
00:41:55,763 --> 00:41:57,807
SHE WON'T PERMIT ME MY LIFE.

773
00:41:57,807 --> 00:41:59,142
I'VE GOT TO LIVE HERS.

774
00:41:59,142 --> 00:42:00,768
JIM.

775
00:42:00,768 --> 00:42:03,271
I HAVE A BEAUTIFUL YEOMAN.

776
00:42:03,271 --> 00:42:05,815
HAVE YOU NOTICED HER, MR. SPOCK?

777
00:42:05,815 --> 00:42:08,985
YOU'RE ALLOWED TO NOTICE HER.

778
00:42:08,985 --> 00:42:11,070
THE CAPTAIN'S NOT PERMITTED.

779
00:42:11,070 --> 00:42:17,869
JIM,
THERE IS AN INTERMIX FORMULA.

780
00:42:19,578 --> 00:42:24,042
NOW I KNOW WHY IT'S CALLED SHE.

781
00:42:24,042 --> 00:42:26,211
IT'S NEVER BEEN TESTED.

782
00:42:26,211 --> 00:42:30,173
IT'S A THEORETICAL RELATIONSHIP
BETWEEN TIME AND ANTIMATTER.

783
00:42:30,173 --> 00:42:36,304
FLESH WOMAN TO TOUCH, TO HOLD.

784
00:42:36,304 --> 00:42:39,682
A BEACH TO WALK ON.

785
00:42:39,682 --> 00:42:43,186
A FEW DAYS,
NO BRAID ON MY SHOULDER.

786
00:42:43,186 --> 00:42:44,937
CAPTAIN.

787
00:42:44,937 --> 00:42:49,984
SCOTTY, HELP.

788
00:42:51,361 --> 00:42:52,904
STAND BY TO INTERMIX.

789
00:42:52,904 --> 00:42:54,822
I'LL CALL THE FORMULAE
IN FROM THE BRIDGE.

790
00:42:54,822 --> 00:42:56,449
Entering upper stratosphere,
Captain.

791
00:42:56,449 --> 00:43:00,828
Skin temperature
now 2,170 degrees.

792
00:43:00,828 --> 00:43:04,332
I'VE GOT TO HANG ON.

793
00:43:05,041 --> 00:43:06,376
TELL THEM.

794
00:43:06,376 --> 00:43:09,921
CLEAR THE CORRIDORS,
THE TURBO LIFT.

795
00:43:09,921 --> 00:43:13,299
HURRY.

796
00:43:26,812 --> 00:43:31,943
NEVER LOSE YOU. NEVER.

797
00:43:48,751 --> 00:43:51,670
BRIDGE.

798
00:43:51,670 --> 00:43:55,425
[ MUSIC ]

799
00:43:57,343 --> 00:44:00,096
[ BEEPING ]

800
00:44:39,885 --> 00:44:41,429
ENGINE ROOM.

801
00:44:41,429 --> 00:44:45,517
WE'RE SET.

802
00:44:47,435 --> 00:44:50,062
HYPERBOLIC COURSE.

803
00:44:50,062 --> 00:44:51,981
DIRECTION, SIR?

804
00:44:51,981 --> 00:44:56,110
DIRECTION. DIRECTION.
IT DOESN'T MATTER.

805
00:44:56,110 --> 00:44:59,322
THE WAY WE CAME.

806
00:45:00,365 --> 00:45:03,784
COURSE LAID IN, SIR.

807
00:45:05,662 --> 00:45:07,788
FUEL TEMPERATURE.

808
00:45:07,788 --> 00:45:09,123
LEVEL.

809
00:45:09,123 --> 00:45:12,544
[ BEEPING ]

810
00:45:20,218 --> 00:45:23,804
NO BEACH TO WALK ON.

811
00:45:24,805 --> 00:45:27,850
SIR?

812
00:45:27,850 --> 00:45:31,937
RAISE ANTIMATTER 840 DEGREES.

813
00:45:31,937 --> 00:45:33,730
THAT'LL TAKE FOUR MINUTES.

814
00:45:33,730 --> 00:45:36,901
WE HAVEN'T THE TIME.
WE'LL HAVE TO RISK IT.

815
00:45:36,901 --> 00:45:40,279
BRIDGE, WE'RE READY.

816
00:45:42,699 --> 00:45:45,742
ENGAGE.

817
00:46:45,595 --> 00:46:47,305
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT, JIM?

818
00:46:47,305 --> 00:46:49,223
ARE YOU?

819
00:46:49,223 --> 00:46:50,642
WE FOUND A CURE.

820
00:46:50,642 --> 00:46:51,850
WE'RE OVER THAT PART OF IT.

821
00:46:51,850 --> 00:46:54,479
OBVIOUSLY, WE WERE SUCCESSFUL.

822
00:46:54,479 --> 00:46:55,772
THE ENGINES IMPLODED.

823
00:46:55,772 --> 00:46:59,816
CAPTAIN, MY VELOCITY GAUGE
IS OFF THE SCALE.

824
00:46:59,816 --> 00:47:02,069
ENGINE POWER
WENT OFF THE SCALE AS WELL.

825
00:47:02,069 --> 00:47:03,946
WE'RE NOW TRAVELING FASTER
THAN IS POSSIBLE

826
00:47:03,946 --> 00:47:06,616
FOR NORMAL SPACE.

827
00:47:06,616 --> 00:47:10,578
CHECK ELAPSED TIME, MR. SULU.

828
00:47:13,372 --> 00:47:17,168
MY CHRONOMETER'S
RUNNING BACKWARDS, SIR.

829
00:47:17,168 --> 00:47:20,630
[ MUSIC ]

830
00:47:23,675 --> 00:47:26,218
TIME WARP.

831
00:47:29,639 --> 00:47:33,100
WE'RE GOING BACKWARD IN TIME.

832
00:47:41,776 --> 00:47:45,488
HELM, BEGIN REVERSING POWER.

833
00:47:50,326 --> 00:47:53,663
SLOWLY.

834
00:47:53,663 --> 00:47:56,165
HELM ANSWERING, SIR.

835
00:47:56,165 --> 00:47:59,627
POWER REVERSING.

836
00:48:14,642 --> 00:48:19,188
WE'RE BACK TO NORMAL TIME,
CAPTAIN.

837
00:48:19,188 --> 00:48:21,065
ENGINES AHEAD.

838
00:48:21,065 --> 00:48:24,235
WARP ONE.

839
00:48:24,235 --> 00:48:26,445
WARP ONE, SIR.

840
00:48:26,445 --> 00:48:27,904
MR. SPOCK.

841
00:48:27,904 --> 00:48:29,323
YES, SIR.

842
00:48:29,323 --> 00:48:32,410
THE TIME WARP.

843
00:48:32,410 --> 00:48:33,619
WHAT DID IT DO TO US?

844
00:48:33,619 --> 00:48:36,247
WE'VE REGRESSED IN TIME
71 HOURS.

845
00:48:36,247 --> 00:48:39,500
IT IS NOW 3 DAYS AGO, CAPTAIN.

846
00:48:39,500 --> 00:48:44,547
WE HAVE 3 DAYS
TO LIVE OVER AGAIN.

847
00:48:47,924 --> 00:48:50,344
NOT THOSE LAST THREE DAYS.

848
00:48:50,344 --> 00:48:53,681
THIS DOES OPEN SOME
INTRIGUING PROSPECTS, CAPTAIN.

849
00:48:53,681 --> 00:48:57,476
SINCE THE FORMULA WORKED,
WE CAN GO BACK IN TIME

850
00:48:57,476 --> 00:49:01,230
TO ANY PLANET, ANY ERA.

851
00:49:01,230 --> 00:49:05,234
WE MAY RISK IT SOMEDAY,
MR. SPOCK.

852
00:49:05,234 --> 00:49:06,819
RESUME COURSE
TO OUR NEXT DESTINATION,

853
00:49:06,819 --> 00:49:07,986
MR. SULU.

854
00:49:07,986 --> 00:49:11,240
COURSE LAID IN, SIR.

855
00:49:11,240 --> 00:49:14,744
STEADY AS SHE GOES.

856
00:49:33,512 --> 00:49:37,934
[ MUSIC ]
